<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="A" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Arrest1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Arrest,</orth> vb. (cf. <emph>'rest</emph>) 1) to seize, to apprehend a person by virtue of the law: <bibl n="shak. mm 1.2.60" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. I, 2, 60</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. err 4.1.69" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. IV, 1, 69</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. err 4.1.69" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. IV, 1, 69</bibl> <bibl n="shak. err 4.1.69" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. IV, 1, 69</bibl> <bibl n="shak. err 4.2.43" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 2, 43</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. err 4.2.43" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 2, 43</bibl> <bibl n="shak. err 4.4.85" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 4, 85</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. err 5.230.85" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 230</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 3.4.360" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. III, 4, 360</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 2.1.9" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B II, 1, 9</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 2.1.9" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B II, 1, 9</bibl> <bibl n="shak. h5 2.2.143" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 II, 2, 143</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.1.136" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B III, 1, 136</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 5.1.136" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 136</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 4.2.13" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 IV, 2, 13</bibl>. The cause of the seizure sometimes expressed by the prep. <emph>on</emph>: <cit><quote>he --s him on it,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mm 1.4.66" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. I, 4, 66</bibl></cit>; <cit><quote>--ed on a band,</quote> <bibl n="shak. err 4.2.49" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. IV, 2, 49</bibl></cit>; <cit><quote>I a. thee on capital treason,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lr 5.3.82" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. V, 3, 82</bibl></cit>; more frequently by <emph>of</emph>: <cit><quote>of capital treason we a. you,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r2 4.151" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 IV, 151</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 4.2.107" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B IV, 2, 107</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 2.2.145" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 II, 2, 145</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.1.97" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B III, 1, 97</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 5.1.106" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 106</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 1.1.201" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 I, 1, 201</bibl>.<lb />2) to seize a thing for debt: <cit><quote>his horses are --ed for it,</quote> <bibl n="shak. wiv 5.5.119" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. V, 5, 119</bibl></cit>.
<lb />3) <emph>I arrest your word</emph> == I take you at your word: <bibl n="shak. mm 2.4.134" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. II, 4, 134</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 2.160" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL II, 160</bibl>.
